🚀 Features
🏠 Homepage: Displays a list of available items fetched from a JSON server.

🛒 Bag Page: Lets users add and view items in their shopping bag.

🔁 Redux Toolkit: Manages app-wide state like items, fetch status, and the shopping bag.

🌐 React Router: Handles routing between pages (/, /bag).

📦 Asynchronous Fetch: Loads data once from the server and caches it using Redux state.

⏳ Loading Indicator: Displays a spinner while data is being fetched.

🧠 Tech Stack
React

React Router DOM

Redux Toolkit

Vite (development server)

Custom JSON API server (localhost:8080)


src/
├── components/         # Reusable UI components (Header, Footer, Spinner)
├── routes/             # Page-level components (Home, Bag, App layout)
├── store/              # Redux slices and store config
│   ├── itemSlice.js
│   ├── bagSlice.js
│   └── fetchStatusSlice.js
├── index.js            # Entry point
├── App.jsx             # Layout + routing wrapper
